## 🌍 Human Evolution Overview
- Human evolution is the long process by which modern humans developed from apelike ancestors.
- Evidence shows this process spans about **six million years**.
- The study involves multiple disciplines: anthropology, paleontology, and genetics.  [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_evolution)  [Britannica](https://www.britannica.com/science/human-evolution)  [Smithsonian National Museum of Natural History](https://humanorigins.si.edu/education/introduction-human-evolution)

---

## 🧬 Key Traits That Define Humans
- Bipedalism: Walking upright on two legs, evolved over 4 million years ago.
- Tool use: Early humans made and used stone tools.
- Large brain: Enabled problem-solving, planning, and abstract thought.
- Language: Complex communication systems developed relatively recently.
- Culture: Symbolic expression, art, and diverse traditions emerged in the last 100,000 years.  [Smithsonian National Museum of Natural History](https://humanorigins.si.edu/education/introduction-human-evolution)

---

## 🧑‍🔬 Major Species in Human Lineage
| Species | Time Period | Significance |
|---------|-------------|--------------|
| **Australopithecus** | 4–2 million years ago | Early bipedal ancestors |
| **Homo habilis** | 2.4–1.4 million years ago | Known as “handy man,” used tools |
| **Homo erectus** | 1.8 million–300,000 years ago | Spread from Africa to Eurasia |
| **Neanderthals** | 400,000–40,000 years ago | Close relatives, interbred with humans |
| **Homo sapiens** | ~350,000 years ago–present | Modern humans, global expansion |

---

## 🔑 Key Insights
- Human evolution was **not linear** but more like a **web**, with interbreeding between species such as Neanderthals and Denisovans.  [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_evolution)
- The **“Out of Africa” theory** suggests modern humans originated in Africa and migrated worldwide.  [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_evolution)

